12/01/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- On Friday (10 January), the Turkish Ministry of Foreign Affairs declared its support for negotiations between Turkish and Greek Cypriots. In an official statement, the ministry said that negotiations should start in the near future, led by UN Secretary General Kofi Annan's special envoy, Alvaro de Soto. The statement also announced that two joint commissions had been set up with the self-proclaimed "Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus" in order to facilitate the process. Turkey's ultimate goal is to find a compromise suitable to both communities on the divided island, the foreign ministry said. (Anadolu Agency, Turkish Daily News - 11/01/03)
